request.description:
Create a new admin user. Use this to create the first admin.

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
    "username": "admin"
  }
}
```

Login with admin credentials. Returns a JWT token that is automatically saved to collection variables.

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "user": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "username": "admin"
    }
  }
}
```

Get all active devices. Requires JWT authentication (Admin only).

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "devices": [
      {
        "_id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
        "fcmToken": "token1",
        "deviceType": "android",
        "isActive": true,
        "createdAt": "2025-03-20T10:00:00.000Z",
        "updatedAt": "2025-03-20T10:00:00.000Z"
      }
    ],
    "total": 1
  }
}
```

Get device statistics including total, active, inactive, and platform breakdown. Requires JWT authentication (Admin only).

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "total": 150,
    "active": 120,
    "inactive": 30,
    "byPlatform": {
      "android": 80,
      "ios": 40
    }
  }
}
```

Deactivate a device (soft delete). Requires JWT authentication (Admin only).

**Path Parameter:**
- `fcmToken`: The FCM token of the device to deactivate

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "device": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "fcmToken": "token-to-deactivate",
      "isActive": false
    }
  }
}
```

Permanently delete inactive devices older than specified days. Requires JWT authentication (Admin only).

**Request Body:**
- `daysOld` (optional): Number of days (default: 30)

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "deletedCount": 15
  }
}
```

Get all messages sorted by pinned status (pinned first) and creation date. No authentication required.

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "messages": [
      {
        "_id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
        "message": "Welcome to JAAP!",
        "link": "https://example.com",
        "isPinned": true,
        "scheduledAt": null,
        "isSent": false,
        "createdAt": "2025-03-20T10:30:00.000Z",
        "updatedAt": "2025-03-20T10:30:00.000Z"
      }
    ],
    "total": 1
  }
}
```

Delete a message by ID. Requires JWT authentication.

**Path Parameter:**
- `id`: MongoDB ObjectId of the message

**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Request successful",
  "data": {
    "message": {
      "_id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "message": "Deleted message",
      "isPinned": false,
      "isSent": false
    },
    "deleted": true
  }
}
```
